%N A395402 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k)^2 + Omega(k)^2.
%e A395402 352 is a term since sigma(352) = 756 = 576 + 12^2 + 6^2 = psi(352) + tau(352)^2 + Omega(352)^2.
%o A395402 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f)^2 + bigomega(f)^2; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 21 2026
